    "narrative": "With a thin schedule today, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on **Colt Keith** (66.33) and **Chase Meidroth** (62.08) to anchor our offensive output. **Colt Keith** stands as the premier start, benefiting from a high-leverage leadoff spot and a soft matchup against Abel. The 7% boost from the SP skill profile, combined with the favorable park factor, makes him our most reliable source of runs and RBI. **Chase Meidroth** remains a strong play assuming he secures the leadoff spot; while the matchup against Lugo carries a slight dynamic platoon penalty, the projected wind out (5%) and his high contact floor keep his efficiency score well above our starting threshold. \n\nWe are currently navigating a significant \"dead zone\" in our roster availability, as key contributors like **Yordan Alvarez**, **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Trea Turner** are inactive today. Consequently, we are forced to bench our primary SB specialists\u2014specifically **Victor Scott II**, **Caleb Durbin**, and **Hyeseong Kim**\u2014due to the lack of games. The most difficult benching decision remains our inability to slot in power bats like **Kyle Schwarber**, **Christian Yelich**, or **Kazuma Okamoto**, whose profiles usually define our ceiling but are currently sidelined by the team's off-day schedule. \n\nOur primary risk factor for this afternoon is the uncertainty surrounding the lineup card for **Chase Meidroth**. Should he fall out of the leadoff position, his projected efficiency score will collapse toward the marginal range, forcing us to reconsider his utility against a veteran arm like Lugo. Elsewhere, we are monitoring the development of **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, **Luis Pena**, **Zac Veen**, and **Lars Nootbaar** to see if they can provide any secondary value, though current projections suggest a quiet day across the board for our depth pieces.",
